<FONT CLASS="title16">Buying </FONT><BR>  

<font class="bodyCopySmall">
Don't buy too much. Cheeses won't last forever in that cold, drafty refrigerator. Buy what you'll eat in about a week (just a few days for fresh cheeses, or a couple of weeks for harder cheeses). 
<P>
Don't buy too little. Remember, some cheeses have rind! If you're buying for a recipe, remember to account for the rind weight. Buy a little extra.
